&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Part time - 16 hours per week&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthuastic person to join our phlebotomy team&lt;br /&gt;to work across all ouh sites including John Radcliffe, Churchill and Horton General Hospital Banbury.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will need to be flexible and have good skills dealing with patients.&lt;br /&gt;We work on wards and in opd so you will not be working in one area.&lt;br /&gt;It would be helpful if you have experience but we will train you to the&lt;br /&gt;required standard.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will need to be able to work mornings, afternoons, weekends as required.&lt;br /&gt;It would be helpful if you hold a drivers licence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 09/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Planned Interview Date: 25/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rachel Sanmarco, Deputy Team Leader, rachel.sanmarco@ouh.nhs.uk 01865 221469&lt;/p&gt;
